      <hedline>
        <hl1>Letters From the Web</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Daniel Rothamel, white teen, responding to Web site questionnaire about racial relations in America, says he is proud to be member of black fraternity Iota Phi</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I'm a brother in the Iota Phi fraternity, the nation's fifth largest historically black Greek organization. It was wonderful for me to gain acceptance into a group with the cultural significance that Iota Phi carries. It might seem an odd statement for a white man to make, but to be embraced by black men and called ''brother'' is the best feeling I have ever experienced.</p>
        <p>Daniel Rothamel  White, 19  Charlottesville, Va.</p>
      </block>
